commit 2a119bafa9c3df05d522c643ea4e7c2ea47bf0f7
Author: Felix-Gong <gongxiaofei24@iscas.ac.cn>
Date:   2026-06-25T03:33:56Z

    riscv: Fix convsusN vsetvli to preserve VL
    
    The convsusN rule's vsetvli calls used rs1=x0 which resets VL to
    VLMAX. The loop's initial vsetvli sets VL based on remaining
    elements, but convsusN's vsetvli overwrites it with VLMAX, causing
    stores to write beyond the intended range and corrupting adjacent
    memory.
    
    Use rs1=VECTOR_LENGTH instead of rs1=x0 to preserve VL.
    
    Part-of: <https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/gstreamer/orc/-/merge_requests/306>

