commit e0b6be3330113c47bf8f3734ed36d5bb5bd7b46c
Author: Felix-Gong <gongxiaofei24@iscas.ac.cn>
Date:   2026-07-11T03:47:39Z

    riscv: Fix convdl narrowing to use truncation (vfncvt.rtz.x.f.w) instead of dynamic rounding
    
    ORC uses emit_vfxncvt_vv for the convdl (double-to-long narrowing
    conversion) opcode, which requires truncating (round-towards-zero)
    semantics to match the C (int) cast used in the emulation path.
    
    The emitter used vs1=0b10001 encoding vfncvt.x.f.w (dynamic rounding
    mode, dependent on the frm CSR), but the RISC-V V spec requires
    vs1=0b10111 for vfncvt.rtz.x.f.w (fixed truncation, round-towards-zero).
    
    This caused all 17 convdl float-to-integer narrowing conversions to
    produce wrong results on RISC-V vector hardware, as the rounding
    mode was undefined (dependent on the frm CSR value at runtime)
    instead of truncating.
    
    Verified on SOPHGO SG2044 (RISC-V RVV 1.0): all 13 ORC tests pass,
    including exec_opcodes_sys which exercises convdl at runtime.
    
    Signed-off-by: Xiaofei Gong <gongxiaofei24@iscas.ac.cn>
    Signed-off-by: YuanSheng <yuansheng@isrc.iscas.ac.cn>
    Part-of: <https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/gstreamer/orc/-/merge_requests/308>

